## **4.2 BACKEND IMPLEMENTATION**

The backend is organized into a modular structure with routes, controllers, models, and middleware.

### **4.2.1 API Endpoints**

The following table summarizes the main API endpoints provided by the backend.

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| POST | /api/auth/register | Register a new user. |
| POST | /api/auth/login | Log in an existing user. |
| GET | /api/resumes | Get all resumes for the logged-in user. |
| POST | /api/resumes | Create a new resume. |
| GET | /api/resumes/:id | Get a specific resume by its ID. |
| PUT | /api/resumes/:id | Update a specific resume. |
| DELETE | /api/resumes/:id | Delete a specific resume. |
| POST | /api/upload | Upload a profile photo. |

